                    <div class="forumpost"><p>Hello Christian,
We have latest plans to start shared IPv4 for free VPS clients with extra custom ports as you have listed for web (similar as normal 80 port for dedicated IPv4). Now all free VPS clients got shared IPv4 only for SSH connection and dedicated IPv6 for all other tasks. We will inform latest updates here.</p>

<p>By the way IPv6 is really standard feature for most internet providers worldwide, we have thousands of free clients all around the world that have no troubles connecting to their VPS. Also make sure that you have installed IPv6 protocol on your PC (for example starting from Winows Vista it is installed by default). Just keep learning and everything is possible! Stay tuned.</p>

<p>P.S. Dark Vader, you're absolutely right, spare your time - get paid plan without worries!</p>
